notes.title: Recipe for Pancakes
notes.content: Mix 1 cup of flour, 1 tbsp of sugar, 2 tsp of baking powder, 1/2 tsp of salt, 1 cup of milk, 1 egg, and 2 tbsp of melted butter. Cook on a hot griddle until golden brown.

notes.title: Fitness Tracker
notes.content: Track daily steps, heart rate, and calories burned. Set a goal of 10,000 steps per day and aim for at least 30 minutes of physical activity.

notes.title: Household Chores
notes.content: Clean the bathroom, vacuum the carpets, dust the furniture, wash the dishes, and do the laundry.

notes.title: Meditation Practice
notes.content: Sit in a quiet place, close your eyes, and focus on your breath. Start with 5 minutes and work your way up to 20 minutes per day.

notes.title: DIY Project
notes.content: Build a bookshelf using reclaimed wood. Use a saw, drill, hammer, nails, and sandpaper to create a custom piece of furniture.

notes.title: Personal Budget
notes.content: Track income and expenses using a spreadsheet. Create categories for rent/mortgage, utilities, groceries, transportation, entertainment, and savings.

notes.title: Garden Planning
notes.content: Research plants that grow well in your climate and soil. Choose a variety of vegetables, fruits, and herbs to grow in raised beds or containers.

notes.title: Language Learning
notes.content: Use a language learning app to practice vocabulary, grammar, and pronunciation. Watch movies and TV shows in the target language to improve comprehension.

notes.title: Job Search
notes.content: Update your resume and cover letter. Research companies in your field and network with professionals on LinkedIn. Apply for jobs and prepare for interviews.
